— BCCI (@BCCI) January 3, 2024

 

SOUTH AFRICA IS ALL-OUT FOR JUST 55!

In a stunning reversal from the first Test, India's pacers, led by Mohammed Siraj, demolished the South African batting line-up in the opening session of the New Year's Test. Siraj's spellbinding performance of 6 for 15, alongside Bumrah's impactful overs, left the Proteas reeling at 55 all out. Despite Dean Elgar's hopes for a solid start after winning the toss in his farewell Test, South Africa's batters fell like dominos, unable to counter India's disciplined and relentless attack. India, seeking redemption from the previous defeat, came back fiercely, marking a dominant display of bowling at lunch on Day 1. 

 

South Africa has faced some swift dismissals against India in Test cricket, with the fewest overs they've been bowled out for occurring in Cape Town in 2024, lasting just 23.2 overs. Previously, Johannesburg in 2006 saw them dismissed in 25.1 overs, while in Nagpur in 2015, they lasted slightly longer, getting bowled out in 33.1 overs.
